<%- include('partials/header', { pageTitle, theme, lang, direction }) %>
<%- include('partials/nav') %>
<% const metrics = aboutMetrics || {}; %>
<main id="main" class="about-page layout">
  <section class="about-hero">
    <div class="about-hero__media">
      <video
        src="/vids/hope-turtle-floating.mp4"
        class="about-hero__video"
        controls
        autoplay
        muted
        loop
        playsinline
        aria-label="Hope Turtle gently floating across the ocean"
      ></video>
    </div>
    <div class="about-hero__body">
      <div class="about-hero__heading">
        <h1>About the Hope Turtle Project</h1>
        <p class="about-hero__subheading">- A human to human intention</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-metrics" aria-label="Hope Turtle platform metrics">
        <article class="metric-card about-metric">
          <span class="metric-label">Turtles</span>
          <span class="metric-value"><%= Number(metrics.turtles || 0).toLocaleString() %></span>
        </article>
        <article class="metric-card about-metric">
          <span class="metric-label">Users</span>
          <span class="metric-value"><%= Number(metrics.users || 0).toLocaleString() %></span>
        </article>
        <article class="metric-card about-metric">
          <span class="metric-label">Boats</span>
          <span class="metric-value"><%= Number(metrics.boats || 0).toLocaleString() %></span>
        </article>
        <article class="metric-card about-metric">
          <span class="metric-label">Hubs</span>
          <span class="metric-value"><%= Number(metrics.hubs || 0).toLocaleString() %></span>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="about-content">
    <p>
      The Hope Turtle Project is an open, regenerative design initiative that combines low-tech ingenuity with
      high-impact humanitarian logistics. It centers on small, autonomous marine drones—nicknamed Hope Turtles—engineered
      to carry aid, messages, or ecological payloads across bodies of water using solar power and sustainable materials
      such as bamboo and recovered plastics. Each Turtle is designed to operate independently or in coordinated
      flotillas, guided by GPS and onboard microcontrollers that log their journey and transmit telemetry data back to a
      shared, transparent database.
    </p>
    <p>
      At its heart, the project aims to demonstrate how community-built, nature-aligned technology can bridge distances
      and deliver hope across seas—without fossil fuels, military infrastructure, or centralized control. By inviting
      local makers, engineers, and communities to replicate, adapt, and deploy their own Hope Turtles, the movement
      fosters decentralized collaboration and resilience. It’s not just about robotics or transport—it’s a living
      experiment in applying ecological ethics, open-source design, and collective compassion to global challenges.
    </p>
    <div class="about-actions">
      <a
        class="button ghost"
        href="https://github.com/russs95/hopeturtles.org/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        View the project on GitHub
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>
<%- include('partials/footer') %>
